        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Israel-Hamas mediation</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/us-secretary-of-state-antony-blinken-us-arab-quint-meeting-egypt-jordan-saudi-arabia.png" alt="US Secretary of State Antony Blinken attended the US-Arab Quint Meeting with representatives from Egypt, Jordan, Saudi Arabia, Qatar, the United Arab Emirates, and the Palestinian Authority" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>US Secretary of State Antony Blinken attended the US-Arab Quint Meeting with representatives from Egypt, Jordan, Saudi Arabia, Qatar, the United Arab Emirates, and the Palestinian Authority. Credits: EVELYN HOCKSTEIN / POOL / AFP</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000"> 
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Before jetting off to Russia, US envoy Steve Witkoff <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-03-2025-h2-2-joined-indirect-talks-in-qatar" target="_blank">joined indirect talks in Qatar</a> between Israel and Hamas on extending the fragile Gaza ceasefire. This marks the first round of negotiations since President Trump took office. The initial 42-day truce saw Hamas release 25 Israeli hostages and five Thai nationals in exchange for 1,800 Palestinian prisoners. 
</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Israel seeks a two-month extension, but Hamas insists on immediate talks to end the war. Israel has blocked aid, including food and fuel, worsening Gaza‚Äôs humanitarian crisis. The UN warns of rising starvation risks. Yemen‚Äôs Houthi rebels have threatened attacks on Israeli-linked ships in response. Israel's PM Benjamin Netanyahu said that Witkoff had proposed a temporary ceasefire extension until after Ramadan and the Jewish holiday of Passover, which the US never confirmed.</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Israeli families of hostages are demanding an urgent ceasefire, while Netanyahu‚Äôs far-right allies are pushing for military action in Gaza. With international pressure mounting, negotiators aim to bridge gaps, but with little success. Hamas views hostages as leverage. Israel moves to the goalpost. So, the situation is almost before the deal, and a resolution is uncertain. </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
