          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>üáµüá± PM Tusk wants Turkey to take a leading role in ending the Ukraine war</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Polish PM Donald Tusk and Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdoƒüan reached a ‚Äúhistoric breakthrough.‚Äù During his visit to Ankara, Tusk asked Turkey to play a key role in <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-03-2025-br2-5-ukraine-russia-peace-efforts" target="_blank">Ukraine-Russia peace efforts</a>. Following discussions in Saudi Arabia, Erdoƒüan proposed that Turkey will help mediate a 30-day ceasefire. He said, ‚ÄúWe must bring about a just end to the war. We are ready to provide a place for peace talks and all possible assistance.‚Äù</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Turkey has maintained a balanced stance since Russia‚Äôs 2022 invasion, keeping ties with Moscow while giving Kyiv arms. Erdoƒüan reaffirmed Turkey‚Äôs commitment to peace talks and EU membership, calling it a strategic goal. As NATO‚Äôs second-largest military, Turkey plays a crucial role in regional security. Tusk pledged Poland‚Äôs support for Turkey‚Äôs EU bid and closer defense cooperation. </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
