          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">What is Balochistan?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/balochistan-region-pakistan-iran-afghanistan-coverage-44-percent-pakistan.png" alt="Balochistan, a region split between Pakistan, Iran, and Afghanistan, covers 44% of Pakistan" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Balochistan, a region split between Pakistan, Iran, and Afghanistan, covers 44% of Pakistan.</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">This week, a group of insurgents held a train carrying over 440 passengers hostage. After a day of fighting between Pakistani forces and <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-03-2025-f1-6-balochistan-separatists" target="_blank">Balochistan separatists</a>, over 300 hostages were released, and 30 insurgents were killed. Balochistan is a region split between Pakistan, Iran, and Afghanistan and has a long history of conflict. The largest part lies in southwestern Pakistan, covering 44% of its land but remains underdeveloped and sparsely populated.
</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The region is named after the Baloch tribe. They have struggled with insurgencies seeking independence since 1948. Since 1948, Baloch nationalists have launched insurgencies against Pakistan. They demand independence and greater autonomy. Despite the region's rich resources, they are frustrated with the economic neglect. Pakistan‚Äôs military has cracked down on separatists, leading to widespread human rights abuses.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The Balochistan Liberation Army attacks Pakistani forces and Chinese investments (CPEC). Pakistan accuses India of supporting separatists. China plays a significant role in Balochistan, mainly through its involvement in the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor. This major infrastructure project aims to connect China‚Äôs Xinjiang province with Pakistan‚Äôs Gwadar port in Balochistan. </p>
          
